-- Rede, Celpa Bonds Tumble After Restructuring Plan Approved
-- B y   V e r o n i c a   N a v a r r o   E s p i n o s a
-- 2012-09-06T16:12:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-06/rede-celpa-bonds-tumble-after-restructuring-plan-approved.html
Bonds issued by  Rede Energia SA (REDE4)  and
its unit Centrais Eletricas do Para SA are falling after the
subsidiary’s creditors approved a restructuring plan.  Rede’s perpetual bonds lost 5.89 cents since the plan was
approved Sept. 1 to 29.33 cents on the dollar as of 1:09 p.m. in
 Sao Paulo . Centrais Eletricas do Para bonds due in 2016 dropped
11.5 cents to 16.83 cents on the dollar, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Veronica Navarro Espinosa in New York at 
 vespinosa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  